---
import FeatureCard from "@components/FeatureCard.astro";
import Link from "@components/links/Link.astro";
import Layout from "@layouts/Layout.astro";
import { Icon } from "astro-icon/components";
---

<Layout page="About">
  <main
    class="relative container flex flex-col gap-24 py-8 text-lg sm:text-xl lg:py-24"
  >
    <div
      class="absolute -top-[50px] -left-1/4 -z-10 aspect-square w-screen bg-[radial-gradient(ellipse_at_50%_50%,_#ff8a0460_0%,#f5ffe1_70%)] sm:w-[700px]"
    >
    </div>
    <header class="flex w-full flex-col gap-6 sm:gap-8 lg:w-2/3">
      <h1
        class="font-title text-4xl tracking-widest uppercase sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl"
      >
        About
      </h1>
      <p class="font-semibold">Art is beautiful, period.</p>
      <p>
        It can provide unique and multidimensional experiences, resonating with
        our feelings, perceptions and thoughts. That's why I've been working in
        software arts for over 10 years, exploring embedded systems, creative
        frameworks, and a dozen programming languages. My artistic projects have
        been exhibited in Brussels, Dakar, Montreal, Dubrovnik, Neuss, Tunis,
        Dublin, Paris and more. It was a lot of fun with nice people! If this
        side interests you, consider visiting my artistic projects on <a
          href="https://jeromeabel.net"
          class="link"
          target="_blank"
          title="jeromeabel.net"
          rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">jeromeabel.net</a
        >.
      </p>
      <p class="font-semibold">
        Software development is a collective and organic exploration of
        humanity.
      </p>
      <p>
        Today, I am fully launching into the field of web development with a
        first specialty in front-end. I just finished a year-long learning
        program at OpenClassrooms, where I learned all the modern tools for
        creating modern, responsive websites: learning skills, writing technical
        specifications, CSS, Sass, creating prototypes in Figma, writing unit
        and integration tests, modern JavaScript and design patterns, making web
        apps with React and Redux.
      </p>
      <p>
        I look forward to growing in this field with brilliant people and
        engineers! <Icon
          name="fluent:handshake-24-regular"
          class="animate-rotate inline-block h-10"
        />
      </p>
      <Link
        label="Download CV"
        href="/CV_JeromeAbel_en.pdf"
        icon="carbon:download"
        variant="textIcon"
        class="bg-black text-white hover:bg-white hover:text-black"
      />
    </header>

    <section class="mt-0 lg:mt-12">
      <h2
        class="font-title text-4xl tracking-widest uppercase sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl"
      >
        My Way Of Doing
      </h2>
      <div
        class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-16 py-8 md:gap-8 lg:grid-cols-3 lg:py-12"
      >
        <FeatureCard id="user" />
        <FeatureCard id="creativity" />
        <FeatureCard id="quality" />
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  a.link {
    border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--color-black);
  }
  a.link:hover {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-black);
  }
  @keyframes animRotation {
    from {
      transform: rotate(-15deg);
    }
    to {
      transform: rotate(15deg);
    }
  }
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .animate-rotate {
      animation: none;
    }
  }
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference) {
    .animate-rotate {
      animation: animRotation 1s ease-in-out infinite alternate;
    }
  }
</style>
